Sec. 148.045. PURCHASE OF SLAUGHTERED CATTLE WITHOUT HIDE OR
EARS. A slaughterer may not purchase cattle that have been
slaughtered by another person if:
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 856 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

(1) the slaughtered animal is not accompanied by the hide
and ears; or
(2) the ear mark or brand on the hide accompanying a
slaughtered animal has been changed, mutilated, or destroyed.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1389, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

